Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp. The month name probably re-cut.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 200, 40 Name Autokrates. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0111.19.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0991)
